result.execSummary:
Rene H. Larios was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Rene H. Larios was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Larios appeared in court in custody from the Columbia County Jail by video w/Aty Allison Borsheim. Defendant would like to waive extradition to the State of TX, Court reviews defendant's extradition rights, Defendant is in agreement w/his rights, understands and would like to waive extradition, Court accepts defendant's waiver, Defendant signs extradition paperwork, Court grants the defendant's extradition to the State of Texas, defendant to remain in the custody of Columbia County Sheriff's Office until State of Texas officials detain defendant
